  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-05 / D3 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "Synthetic V&V 40 credibility package for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. The Output-comparison validation result references an experimental dataset obtained under steady-flow bench conditions at a single mid-range operating point (4 L/min, 3000 RPM) rather than the five flow-speed combinations required by the COU. The comparator is described in the narrative without a comparedAgainst link, and the operating-condition mismatch is not flagged. Decision outcome is recorded as Accepted despite persistent credibility gaps, embedding the W-AR-05 / D3 weakness.",
