      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) reported for hemolysis QoI on at least three systematically refined meshes with GCI < 5% on the fine grid; temporal convergence also demonstrated.",
      "rationale": "Three mesh levels (2.1 M, 6.4 M, 18.7 M cells) were used. Richardson extrapolation yielded GCI of 12.3% on the medium mesh and 8.1% on the fine mesh — above the 5% threshold. Temporal convergence was demonstrated only at the single 4 L/min operating point. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions span all five COU flow-speed combinations; fluid properties, hematocrit, and temperature controlled and reported with uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Available experimental data (Hariharan et al.) cover only a single steady-flow operating point (4 L/min, 3000 RPM). The COU requires five flow-speed combinations including pulsatile-flow conditions at 2 L/min and 5 L/min. Hematocrit and temperature were controlled in the source experiment but not independently verified for this study. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison of CFD-predicted NIH against experimental NIH across all five COU operating points with uncertainty bands overlaid; systematic bias assessed.",
      "rationale": "Quantitative output comparison was performed at the single available experimental condition (4 L/min, 3000 RPM steady flow). Agreement within 18% relative error was documented. No comparison was performed at the remaining four COU operating points. The validation narrative treats the single-point agreement as representative of the full operating envelope without explicitly noting the extrapolation. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation QoI is the absolute NIH value directly comparable to the clinical acceptance threshold; scalar transport formulation traceable to the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power law as used in the COU model.",
      "rationale": "The experimental QoI is normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) expressed in mg/dL, matching the COU clinical threshold metric. However, the experimental NIH was derived from a modified Giersiepen-Wurzinger correlation with different empirical constants than those used in the COU simulation. The discrepancy in constants was acknowledged in a footnote but not propagated as a systematic uncertainty. Achieved level 2 against required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities directly address the Class III VAD operating envelope including pulsatile flow, patient-representative hematocrit range, and all five specified flow-speed combinations.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities were conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under steady-flow bench conditions at one operating point. The Class III VAD COU requires pulsatile inflow waveforms and five operating points. The pump geometry is identical but the hemodynamic loading conditions differ substantially. The validation summary does not explicitly flag this scope limitation. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
